Bugs:

None known.

================================================================

Must-haves:

* A way to automatically close all inputs at exit. Java 1.3 introduces
  Runtime.addShutdownHook(), but we don't want to require Java 1.3.

* Tracing of inner classes,
  e.g. Trace.println("FD.GossipThread.run()", ...)

================================================================

Nice-to-haves:

* Same module output to different logs at the same time for different trace
  levels. (All messages >= trace level output to each log)

* Module name matching using startsWith(). Thus,
  AckMcastReceiverWindow.Foo1(), AckMcastSenderWindow.Bar() and
  AckMcastReceiverWindow.FooBar() could be matched with "AckMcast".

================================================================

Ideas:

* Check for already-existing Tracers in each call to setOutput(). For
  example, if I call Trace.setOutput("Foo", DEBUG, "file") and then
  Trace.setOutput("Bar", DEBUG, "file") it would be nice to re-use the same
  Tracer instead of opening two FileWriters on the same file.

* Method argument handling in module names.

* Cache module name parsing. Perhaps a Module class?
